  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several international laws and initiatives aimed at combating money laundering:\n\n1. The Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n- Establishes global standards for preventing money laundering\n- Recommends international legal and regulatory measures\n- Monitors countries' compliance with anti-money laundering guidelines\n\n2. United Nations Conventions\n- UN Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- UN Convention against Corruption\n- Provide frameworks for international cooperation against money laundering\n\n3. Basel Committee Guidelines\n- Sets banking regulations to prevent financial crimes\n- Promotes transparency in international financial transactions\n\n4. International Monetary Fund (IMF) Standards\n- Provides guidance on financial system regulations\n- Assists countries in developing anti-money laundering frameworks\n\n5. EU Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Establish continent-wide regulations for financial institutions\n- Regularly update requirements for detecting and preventing money laundering\n\nMost countries have domestic laws implementing these international standards, requiring financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n\nThese laws aim to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income.",
